      <description>In the next videos expert Jeremy Blackwell shows you ideas how to remodel a basement. The first video is about basement remodeling project scheduling He suggest to start with the framing and when almost done with it call for the mechanical contractor to finish the heat runs. The next step is finishing the plumbing. After [...]&lt;p&gt;This post via the &lt;a href="http://basementdesignpro.com"&gt;Basement Design&lt;/a&gt; blog where you can get basement remodeling tips, ideas and informations.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;a href="http://basementdesignpro.com/basement-remodeling/how-to-remodel-basement/"&gt;How to Remodel a Basement&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/basement-design/Basement_Design-How_to_Remodel_a_Basement.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In the next videos expert Jeremy Blackwell shows you ideas <strong>how to remodel a basement</strong>.</p>
<h3>The first video is about basement remodeling project scheduling</h3>
<p><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="445" height="364" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/6FFbRHAfB_c&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x2b405b&amp;color2=0x6b8ab6&amp;border=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="445" height="364" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/6FFbRHAfB_c&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x2b405b&amp;color2=0x6b8ab6&amp;border=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object></p>
<p>He suggest to start with the framing and when almost done with it call for the mechanical contractor to finish the heat runs.</p>
<p>The next step is finishing the plumbing. After that electrical works coming before covering with sheet rock.</p>
<p>When you finish these start the insulation then the dry walls.</p>
<h3>The second video is about framing issues and tips</h3>
<p><object classid="clsid:d27cdb6e-ae6d-11cf-96b8-444553540000" width="445" height="364" codebase="http://download.macromedia.com/pub/shockwave/cabs/flash/swflash.cab#version=6,0,40,0"><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always" /><param name="src" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/3zro0ExKsns&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x2b405b&amp;color2=0x6b8ab6&amp;border=1" /><param name="allowfullscreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="445" height="364" src="http://www.youtube.com/v/3zro0ExKsns&amp;hl=en_US&amp;fs=1&amp;rel=0&amp;color1=0x2b405b&amp;color2=0x6b8ab6&amp;border=1" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object></p>
<p>The first framing idea is find tzhe longest wall and start framing there.</p>
<p>When heat runs hanging down from the ceiling, frame around them to make sure dry wall can hang around.</p>
<p>Jeremy talks about heat ducts as well. He shows how to frame them to leave room for returning airs, because these airs are crucial.</p>
<p>OK, these were two important aspect when you plan <em>how to remodel a basement</em>.</p>
