      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Are you considering a remodeled basement?</p>
<p>Right now, you&#8217;re probably using the basement for storage of old and not used items, so there are not so much space for other activities downstairs.  Those unused items and utilities are going to take up space no matter how well organized it is.</p>
<p>You may have spent a zillion hours to find out what to do.</p>
<p>One solution is to finish only part of your basement. Create an unfinished area and organize your items better. Create more storage space with shelves and cabinets.</p>
<p>Besides there will be another part of the basement where you can create a remodeled section and you can use this for a better purpose then just store stuff.</p>
